summary_markdown: This data presents a comparative analysis of buyers of product X, detailing the percentage of these buyers who also purchased (regular) Coca-Cola during the same period. The structure highlights the overlap in purchasing behavior across different consumer segments for product X. Specifically, it shows that buyers of Diet Coke had a 65% overlap with regular Coca-Cola purchasers, while Fanta buyers showed a 70% overlap. Lift buyers exhibited a 67% overlap, and Pepsi buyers demonstrated the highest overlap at 72%. The average overlap across all analyzed buyer groups for product X and regular Coca-Cola was 69%, indicating a significant cross-purchasing trend.
